        "content": "<p>So I argued that being able to set <code>current-&gt;mm</code> with <code>kthread_use_mm()</code> is not a problem <a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/all/CAH5fLgjuKEU8noU5XN_FWEy4wAzJu0aeaURzNsCQrt59a_0gJA@mail.gmail.com/\">here</a>, but it turns out the argument doesn't fully work:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">current</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">current</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mm</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"n\">kthread_use_mm</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">some_mm</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">||</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">mm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">current</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mm</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"p\">});</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">drop</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">some_mm</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"n\">mm</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">do_stuff</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Ideas?</p>",
        "id": 485089784,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1732883650
